In this introductory chapter of "Game Specs: An Asset Guide for Digital Creators", we have delved into the fundamental aspects of game asset management and utilization. From understanding the concept of Game Families and the grouping of games by development studios to exploring the methods of locating game files and decoding game archives and assets, digital creators are equipped with essential knowledge to navigate the intricate world of game assets. By decoding these proprietary formats and leveraging modern game development platforms like Unity, Unreal Engine, and OpenGL, creators can harness the potential of game assets to create immersive and captivating gaming experiences. This chapter sets the foundation for mastering the art of repurposing game assets and paves the way for unlocking limitless creativity in the realm of digital game development.